    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for tuned.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The tuned packages provide a service that tunes system settings according to a selected profile.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* tuned: `script_pre` and `script_post` options allow to pass arbitrary scripts executed by root (CVE-2024-52336)\n\n* tuned: improper sanitization of `instance_name` parameter of the `instance_create()` method (CVE-2024-52337)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
